		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Beth Alvarado</span></strong> divides her time between Tucson, where she teaches at the University of Arizona, and Bend, Oregon, where she practices her Spanish by reading aloud to a dog named Ollie. She is the author of a memoir, <em>Anthropologies</em>, and a story collection, <em>Not a Matter of Love</em>.</p><a href="/contributors/beth-alvarado" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
